    "This model, proposed in 2023, was trained on a dataset of 137,000 images with aesthetic scores.",
    "The authors of this method indicate that their proposed model outperforms other mainstream models in terms of aesthetic score prediction 49.",
    "We utilized this model to automatically annotate the aesthetic scores of each image in the ADSSFID-49 dataset.",
    "To make the diffusion model easier to train, we normalized all scores using a mapping that adheres to a normal distribution, resulting in integer scores between 1 and 10.",
    "The distribution of aesthetic scores for the processed ADSSFID-49 images can be seen in Fig. 5."
